## Query Basics

### Finding Records

```ruby
# Find by ID
Article.find(1)  # Raises ActiveRecord::RecordNotFound if not found

# Find by attribute
Article.find_by(slug: 'my-article')  # Returns nil if not found
Article.find_by!(slug: 'my-article')  # Raises exception if not found

# Find multiple
Article.find([1, 2, 3])  # Returns array

# First/Last
Article.first
Article.last
Article.first(5)  # First 5 records

# Take (random order)
Article.take
Article.take(10)
```

### Where Queries

```ruby
# Basic where
Article.where(status: 'published')
Article.where(user_id: 1)

# Multiple conditions (AND)
Article.where(status: 'published', user_id: 1)

# String conditions (use with caution - SQL injection risk!)
Article.where("status = ?", 'published')
Article.where("views_count > ?", 1000)

# Array conditions
Article.where("status IN (?)", ['published', 'archived'])

# Hash conditions with ranges
Article.where(created_at: 1.week.ago..Time.current)
Article.where(views_count: 100..1000)

# NOT conditions
Article.where.not(status: 'draft')
Article.where.not(user_id: 1)

# OR conditions
Article.where(status: 'published').or(Article.where(featured: true))
```

